File: The City of Tshwane has been running without a mayor for eight months. eNuus PRETORIA - Gauteng Co-operative governance MEC Lebogang Maile says he won't appeal a Supreme Court of Appeal ruling in favour of the DA in the City of Tshwane.
Maile says the Gauteng government would rather wait for a Constitutional Court decision on the matter. READ: DA welcomes SCA decision to reinstate Tshwane city council Last week, the appeals court ruled his decision to place the metro under administration was unlawful. This means the city has been running without a mayor for eight months.